parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floorboard
the brake pedal extends to the floor
the brake pedal requires maximum effort to engage
the ABS and brake lights illuminate
the ABS does not work when the brake pedal is depressed
the vehicle takes a long time to stop when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate brake performance can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle takes a long time to stop when the brakes are applied
the brakes require extended stopping distance
the vehicle may not stop in time to avoid accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS and brake lights illuminate
the ABS does not work when the brake pedal is depressed
the chime constantly sounds in the vehicle indicating that the ABS does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure: Fuel Line Corrosion and Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel line corrosion and leaks can cause fuel to spill during refueling, increasing the risk of fire in the presence of an ignition source.
symptoms: Strong smell of gasoline after refueling
fuel leaks under the vehicle
fuel spills during refueling
corrosion of the fuel filler pipe.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure: Fuel Line Splitting
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel line splitting can cause fuel to leak under the vehicle, increasing the risk of fire in the presence of an ignition source.
symptoms: Strong smell of gasoline
fuel leaks under the vehicle
fuel spills during refueling
splitting of the fuel line near the muffler.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Belt Separation and Tread Loss
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the tire belt and loss of tread can cause excessive vibration, loss of control, and potentially lead to accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a thumping noise

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Uncontrollable shaking of the vehicle
noise coming from the front of the vehicle
